1
00:00:04,755 --> 00:00:06,923
I ought to have this framed.

2
00:00:07,049 --> 00:00:09,884
My last bill from Princeton.

3
00:00:11,178 --> 00:00:12,470
And I thought
we were celebrating

4
00:00:12,596 --> 00:00:14,263
the fact
that I actually graduated.

5
00:00:14,390 --> 00:00:15,951
I always knew
you'd be able to graduate.

6
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:20,269
What I didn't know was whether
I would be able to pay for it.

7
00:00:20,396 --> 00:00:23,898
Your mom,
she'd be so proud of you.

8
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:26,901
You always say that.

9
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:30,029
I'm so proud of you.
Always was.

10
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,451
Come on, Dad, you're gonna cry.

11
00:00:36,537 --> 00:00:39,163
You wanna be embarrassed?
You got it!

12
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:50,466
Look, don't party
too hard tonight.

13
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,885
Your grandmother wants a picture
of you getting that sheepskin,

14
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:55,252
and it'd be nice if you didn't
look completely hung over.

15
00:00:55,347 --> 00:00:56,639
Oh, no, don't worry,

16
00:00:56,765 --> 00:00:58,391
I've had enough alcohol
in the past week

17
00:00:58,517 --> 00:01:02,019
- to last me another four years.
- Good, I think.

18
00:01:10,988 --> 00:01:13,906
Drink! Drink! Drink!

19
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:17,326
More! More!
Drink! Drink! Drink!

20
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,834
12:55!

21
00:01:27,463 --> 00:01:28,671
Man!

22
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:33,050
- You are the man!
- Tell me something I don't know!

23
00:01:36,013 --> 00:01:37,889
- Hey, that's not funny, man.
- What?

24
00:01:38,015 --> 00:01:41,017
- Yeah, right, you shocked me.
- With what? I got nothing.

25
00:01:46,064 --> 00:01:48,775
Well, hey, whoever's
doing that better cut it out!

26
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:57,283
What the hell's going on?

27
00:01:57,409 --> 00:01:59,889
Maybe there's a short somewhere,
the floor's covered with beer.

28
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:00,953
No way, no,
the outlets are GFI,

29
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:02,663
plus he's got
rubber-soled shoes on.

30
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:07,043
- Oh, my God!
- Somebody call 911!

31
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:53,464
Patient experiences
shock-like sensations

32
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:57,718
as well as headaches, nausea,
and drowsiness.

33
00:02:57,845 --> 00:02:59,136
Shocks?

34
00:02:59,263 --> 00:03:01,138
Excruciatingly painful shocks.

35
00:03:01,265 --> 00:03:03,140
ER docs referred him
to a neurologist,

36
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:05,707
who referred him to five other
doctors in the last seven days.

37
00:03:05,769 --> 00:03:08,354
Shocks could be Lhermitte's sign.
Early symptom of MS.

38
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,648
No. MRI showed
no white matter lesions,

39
00:03:10,774 --> 00:03:13,150
and the shocks aren't
accompanied by neck flexing.

40
00:03:13,277 --> 00:03:15,319
- Good morning!
- It's almost noon.

41
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,613
Really? That must be
why I'm so hungry.

42
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:18,781
Who's up for lunch?

43
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:20,199
What's with the jacket?

44
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:23,870
It keeps me warm and cool.
How does it know?

45
00:03:23,996 --> 00:03:25,317
We're discussing
your new patient.

46
00:03:25,414 --> 00:03:28,214
Must be a boring discussion, seeing
as I haven't accepted a new patient.

47
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:31,419
You accepted him the moment
I loaned you 5 grand.

48
00:03:31,545 --> 00:03:33,045
Oh, wait, wait.

49
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:35,715
When I said I'd do anything for the
money, obviously I didn't mean it.

50
00:03:35,841 --> 00:03:38,551
You're gonna like this. The kid's
getting shocked every few minutes.

51
00:03:38,677 --> 00:03:40,136
Why would you need $5,000?

52
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:43,139
Bad night at poker,
or great night with a hooker?

53
00:03:43,265 --> 00:03:44,640
Thank you for saving me
the trouble

54
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:48,227
of deflecting that personal
question with a joke.

55
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:50,146
College student?

56
00:03:50,272 --> 00:03:52,148
Nitrous oxide's fun at parties.

57
00:03:52,274 --> 00:03:54,483
Caused the shocks, and drinking
till we puke every night

58
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:55,693
can cause everything else.

59
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:57,236
- Give him some B12.
- Been there, done that.

60
00:03:57,362 --> 00:04:00,364
Also ruled out cancer,
MS, pyridoxine toxicity,

61
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:02,617
and all the popular
neuropathies.

62
00:04:03,368 --> 00:04:06,162
- Cervical spondylosis.
- Doesn't explain the low white count.

63
00:04:06,288 --> 00:04:07,622
He's black.

64
00:04:07,748 --> 00:04:10,750
I'm assuming he's not just really
dirty, but is of African descent,

65
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:12,209
which means he'd have
a lower white count.

66
00:04:12,336 --> 00:04:14,545
- Not this low.
- He's a wrestler.

67
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,839
Probably uses diuretics
to cut weight.

68
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:17,965
That can also cause
low white count.

69
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,884
Not this low. "Not this low."

70
00:04:20,010 --> 00:04:21,510
Behcet's. No skin lesions.

71
00:04:21,637 --> 00:04:24,931
- Cervical herpes zoster, myelitis...
- No external outbreak.

72
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:31,103
Something's missing.
Find out what it is.

73
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:34,190
- I don't even know what that means.
- Well, figure it out.

74
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:37,234
Find it out, and then find me.
I'll be at lunch.

75
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,821
- No ideas?
- Lots of ideas.

76
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:43,282
Too many ideas,
that's why so many tests.

77
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:46,494
Have you used
any recreational drugs?

78
00:04:49,581 --> 00:04:53,042
What? I'm gonna get
mad at you for getting stoned?

79
00:04:53,168 --> 00:04:54,877
Not today, not here.

80
00:04:57,965 --> 00:05:01,133
At Christmas, one of the
guys had some ecstasy,

81
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:02,139
I mean, I... It was...

82
00:05:07,265 --> 00:05:08,933
Son of a bitch!

83
00:05:14,398 --> 00:05:16,941
ANA is negative for lupus,
again.

84
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:20,695
House wants more information, not the
same information done over again.

85
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:21,862
"Find what's missing."

86
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:24,448
For all we know, the kid is dying
and he's giving us riddles?

87
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:26,993
Did a more detailed history,
went back three generations.

88
00:05:27,119 --> 00:05:28,703
- And?
- His mom died in a car accident,

89
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:30,871
his mom's mom had arthritis,
and his mom's mom's dad

90
00:05:30,998 --> 00:05:33,374
served in an all-black
tank battalion under Patton.

91
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:36,085
Fascinating. If it's not a
tumor, it has to be MS.

92
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:37,128
Wilson already ruled out...

93
00:05:37,254 --> 00:05:39,588
MRI can't rule out
MS 100% of the time.

94
00:05:39,715 --> 00:05:42,842
- Doesn't explain the low white count.
- Alcoholism does.

95
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:46,387
On admission, his BAC was 2.0,
liver enzymes off the chart.

96
00:05:46,513 --> 00:05:49,390
It was graduation weekend. He barely
drank in the weeks before that,

97
00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:51,892
and he didn't drink at all
during his wrestling season.

98
00:05:52,019 --> 00:05:53,936
- If you believe him.
- I did a tox screen...

99
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:56,902
It doesn't matter if she believes him
or not, it's already in the chart.

100
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:59,400
We're supposed to find out
what's missing.

101
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:09,702
Well, this... This is perfect.

102
00:06:09,828 --> 00:06:12,121
Invite me to dinner
on Thursday night.

103
00:06:12,247 --> 00:06:15,124
Come on, we haven't had
a nice meal together since...

104
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:18,836
Yesterday, when I loaned you
$5,000 to buy a new car.

105
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:20,254
My treat.

106
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:25,134
Two-wheeled vehicles
that travel 150 miles an hour

107
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:28,387
don't really go well with crippled,
irresponsible drug addicts.

108
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:32,349
Actually, two-wheeled vehicles that go
180 miles an hour do not go well

109
00:06:32,476 --> 00:06:34,435
with healthy,
responsible architects

110
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:36,645
who don't know how to
separate braking and turning.

111
00:06:36,772 --> 00:06:39,148
Good news is, it brings
the price right down.

112
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:41,942
- You're taking it back.
- Mom!

113
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:44,487
How about we talk
about this over dinner?

114
00:06:44,613 --> 00:06:46,614
Forget dinner,
you're gonna kill yourself!

115
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:49,283
- Nice bike!
- Thank you.

116
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:53,496
See, that's how you do it.
Compliments, dinner.

117
00:06:53,622 --> 00:06:55,498
What do you do with your cane?

118
00:06:55,624 --> 00:06:57,458
If he buys me dinner,
he'll find out.

119
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,131
Evel Knievel
had the same setup.

120
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:05,966
And he broke every bone
in his body.

121
00:07:06,093 --> 00:07:09,386
We went through all the imaging
studies and redid the blood cultures.

122
00:07:09,513 --> 00:07:12,139
I don't want hand-me-downs,
I want brand-new stuff.

123
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:15,476
Well, there's nothing...
There's nothing missing!

124
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:18,270
Sorry, I didn't
catch that last part!

125
00:07:19,314 --> 00:07:21,816
There's... There's...

126
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,156
There's nothing else we can do.

127
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:31,242
- Did you check the police report?
- On what?

128
00:07:31,368 --> 00:07:32,827
On his mom's car accident.

129
00:07:32,953 --> 00:07:35,162
That was 15 years ago. The
kid wasn't even in the car.

130
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:37,873
She veered off a straight,
dry road in broad daylight.

131
00:07:37,999 --> 00:07:39,159
That doesn't seem odd to you?

132
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,727
She probably got distracted changing
radio stations or something.

133
00:07:41,837 --> 00:07:43,077
That's what the police thought.

134
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:45,131
Of course, they didn't know
that she has a family member

135
00:07:45,257 --> 00:07:48,134
who is frequently incapacitated
by shock-like sensations.

136
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:51,345
- A genetic component seems unlikely.
- But it's interesting.

137
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,848
Type II neurofibromatosis
could cause the shocks.

138
00:07:53,974 --> 00:07:55,266
You knew this was missing?

139
00:07:55,392 --> 00:07:58,144
I knew something was missing,
maybe this, maybe something else.

140
00:07:58,270 --> 00:08:01,438
Get a DNA analysis of the
long arm of chromosome 22.

141
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:08,028
You'd rather have dinner with your wife?

142
00:08:08,155 --> 00:08:11,740
Yes, I would.
If she were speaking to me.

143
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,536
Unlike her, I could make
it worth your while.

144
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:18,497
Fine.

145
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:20,749
Shall I drive?

146
00:08:21,877 --> 00:08:23,169
No.

147
00:08:23,295 --> 00:08:26,547
And I'm not letting you in my
car until I see your wallet.

148
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,594
NF2. It's an inherited disease.

149
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:35,139
It could cause abnormal growths
on the cranial nerves.

150
00:08:35,265 --> 00:08:37,106
It would explain the shocks
and other symptoms.

151
00:08:37,142 --> 00:08:39,059
DNA analysis will show
whether your son

152
00:08:39,186 --> 00:08:40,936
has the specific
chromosome mutation

153
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,146
which causes the disease.

154
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:45,315
But if it's inherited, that means someone
else in our family would have it.

155
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:46,942
We think your wife
may have had it.

156
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:49,445
No. She never had
any sort of health problems.

157
00:08:49,571 --> 00:08:52,031
No odd-looking freckles,
nodules in the iris?

158
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:54,241
Nothing. I mean, why would
you think she was sick?

159
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:57,494
We think it may have been
what caused her car accident.

160
00:08:57,621 --> 00:09:00,247
Wait, what do you mean? My mom's
car was hit by a drunk driver.

161
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:03,125
That's not what
the police report indicated.

162
00:09:04,628 --> 00:09:07,254
Well, you must have gotten
the wrong report.

163
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,715
No. They didn't.

164
00:09:16,765 --> 00:09:19,225
When you started driving...

165
00:09:19,351 --> 00:09:20,351
I...

166
00:09:22,187 --> 00:09:23,938
You lied about how Mom died?

167
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:26,345
I figured if her death could
somehow mean something, it...

168
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,235
How does lying about it
mean something?

169
00:09:29,361 --> 00:09:31,820
How could you use her
like that, Dad? Her death?

170
00:09:31,947 --> 00:09:35,032
- I was just trying to protect you.
- What else isn't true?

171
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,243
She wasn't a teacher,
you just wanted me to read?

172
00:09:37,369 --> 00:09:38,744
What's that smell?

173
00:09:39,371 --> 00:09:41,372
I don't smell...

174
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:47,127
We're gonna need a nurse.

175
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:50,589
- What the hell?
- It's okay. We'll take care of it.

176
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:52,258
You didn't feel anything?

177
00:09:52,384 --> 00:09:53,384
No.

178
00:09:56,388 --> 00:09:58,055
- You feel that?
- Yeah.

179
00:09:58,181 --> 00:09:59,890
But you didn't feel
any of this?

180
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,016
No.

181
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:15,364
Sphincter paralysis plus shocks
equals Miller Fisher Syndrome.

182
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:16,865
Not if you add
the stool sample,

183
00:10:16,992 --> 00:10:18,242
which is negative
for C. Jejuni.

184
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:21,495
He lied to his son
about how his mom died?

185
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:23,247
He was just protecting him.

186
00:10:23,373 --> 00:10:24,707
Manipulating him.

187
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:27,418
- That's what parents do.
- They lie to us because they love us.

188
00:10:27,544 --> 00:10:28,752
Who's getting teary?

189
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:30,254
Mom's death is irrelevant.

190
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:32,089
DNA revealed no NF2 markers

191
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:33,632
or any other inherited disease.

192
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:36,343
Apparently, she really did
fall asleep at the wheel.

193
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:39,138
So, what exactly
are we talking about here?

194
00:10:39,264 --> 00:10:43,100
A little peeker, or did the prairie
dog actually come out to play?

195
00:10:43,226 --> 00:10:45,561
- Excuse me?
- Are we talking explosive?

196
00:10:46,396 --> 00:10:48,856
The hemoccult
was negative for blood,

197
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:53,861
and I wouldn't say he actually exploded.
More like gushed?

198
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,071
Good, then we're
getting somewhere.

199
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,239
Yeah? Where?

200
00:10:57,365 --> 00:10:59,241
I have no idea.

201
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,367
- Of course.
- Hello?

202
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:02,828
- Love the riddles.
- Hi, Mom.

203
00:11:02,954 --> 00:11:04,902
Look, I have a business
dinner on Thursday night.

204
00:11:04,915 --> 00:11:06,874
I can't get out of it.

205
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,377
I know, I really
wanted to see you, too.

206
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:15,257
Actually, can I call you back?
I'm in a meeting right now.

207
00:11:15,383 --> 00:11:16,759
Okay, thanks.

208
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:19,720
Who was that?

209
00:11:19,846 --> 00:11:21,263
Angelina Jolie.

210
00:11:21,389 --> 00:11:24,558
I call her "Mom".
Who thinks that's sexy?

211
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:26,685
So, explosive or gushing...

212
00:11:26,811 --> 00:11:29,021
She never calls here,
is everything okay?

213
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,274
Great, yeah.

214
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,360
My dad's taking her to Europe.

215
00:11:34,486 --> 00:11:36,904
They got a nine-hour layover
in Newark on Thursday.

216
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:40,282
- If it's gastrointestinal...
- You lied to avoid seeing your own mom.

217
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:43,660
Are you kidding?
I can't lie to my mom.

218
00:11:43,787 --> 00:11:45,162
Seriously, I can't.

219
00:11:45,288 --> 00:11:46,497
Wilson's invited me to dinner.

220
00:11:46,623 --> 00:11:49,166
It'd be rude to stand up a guy
who just loaned me 5 grand.

221
00:11:49,292 --> 00:11:51,085
Transverse myelitis.

222
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:53,420
Could cause numbness,
anal sphincter dysfunction,

223
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:54,546
and the shocks.

224
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:57,299
Thank you for taking
no interest in my mother.

225
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:58,801
But that begs the question,

226
00:11:58,927 --> 00:12:01,178
what caused
the transverse myelitis?

227
00:12:01,304 --> 00:12:03,555
Well, we've ruled out
cancer and MS.

228
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:04,848
Leaves infection.

229
00:12:04,974 --> 00:12:06,350
If there was infection,
there'd be a fever.

230
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:08,356
And his blood and CSF cultures
are all negative.

231
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:11,688
Maybe the infection's gone
but the memory remains.

232
00:12:12,399 --> 00:12:14,274
Molecular mimicry.

233
00:12:14,401 --> 00:12:15,776
Nice.

234
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:19,405
Okay, get an immunoglobulin
level and electrophoresis.

235
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:26,870
You're good, my friend.
I'm sure we'll meet again.

236
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:30,249
Do you really think
that was his mom on the phone?

237
00:12:30,375 --> 00:12:33,168
Probably, don't know
why he'd lie about that.

238
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:34,253
Who cares?

239
00:12:34,379 --> 00:12:36,880
You're not the least bit curious
what his parents are like?

240
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:38,367
I'm sure his mom's
a piece of work.

241
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:40,134
Only a mother
could do that much damage.

242
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:41,885
My bet's he was born
the way he is.

243
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:44,263
Probably tormented his parents,
not the other way around.

244
