565
00:26:27,544 --> 00:26:29,379
He said he can't leave work.

566
00:26:29,505 --> 00:26:31,339
Yeah, you told me that
two hours ago.

567
00:26:31,465 --> 00:26:32,924
I'm not gonna lie.

568
00:26:33,050 --> 00:26:35,969
Why, 'cause it's wrong?
Or because you're a coward?

569
00:26:36,095 --> 00:26:37,178
Tough choice.

570
00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:40,098
You'd be wasting two hours
of the kid's time.

571
00:26:40,224 --> 00:26:43,142
Is that deeply and unforgivably
morally wrong? No.

572
00:26:43,269 --> 00:26:46,688
Because it's not a waste of his time.
Unless we're wrong.

573
00:26:46,814 --> 00:26:50,275
Unless his condition's got
nothing to do with his friend's.

574
00:26:50,401 --> 00:26:52,944
You're just afraid
of being wrong.

575
00:26:56,657 --> 00:26:58,366
Your parents called.

576
00:26:59,743 --> 00:27:02,704
- They had to catch an earlier...
- You don't have to lie to him.

577
00:27:02,830 --> 00:27:03,830
Kid's on his way here.

578
00:27:03,956 --> 00:27:04,956
He got off work?

579
00:27:05,082 --> 00:27:09,085
Yeah, by vomiting blood.
Ambulance is 10 minutes out.

580
00:27:16,552 --> 00:27:18,136
- You Taddy?
- Why?

581
00:27:18,846 --> 00:27:21,055
Love the name.
If I ever had a dog.

582
00:27:21,181 --> 00:27:22,307
Take off his pants.

583
00:27:22,433 --> 00:27:23,433
Hey.

584
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:24,976
Don't talk to her,
listen to me.

585
00:27:25,102 --> 00:27:26,978
He's vomited in excess
of three units of blood.

586
00:27:27,104 --> 00:27:29,147
- He needs to be admitted before...
- If you wanted to be a doctor,

587
00:27:29,273 --> 00:27:31,793
maybe you should have buckled down
a little more in high school.

588
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:33,140
- Bite me.
- What are you doing?

589
00:27:33,193 --> 00:27:34,986
Exactly how close
were you and Carnell?

590
00:27:35,112 --> 00:27:35,987
Not so close.

591
00:27:36,113 --> 00:27:37,864
Spend a lot of time together
in Jamaica?

592
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:38,990
Share a room?

593
00:27:39,116 --> 00:27:41,993
Wait, you don't think...
Look, we're not gay.

594
00:27:42,119 --> 00:27:45,246
- I'm not saying you're gay.
- I'm saying you had sex.

595
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:47,290
Look, we're not gay.
We hardly even hung out.

596
00:27:47,416 --> 00:27:49,083
Right. Guess you just
flew him down to Jamaica

597
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:50,209
'cause he won a contest.

598
00:27:50,336 --> 00:27:51,753
No, he's in my frat.

599
00:27:51,879 --> 00:27:53,171
All right,
between school and wrestling

600
00:27:53,297 --> 00:27:55,965
and going home every break to
work in his father's junkyard,

601
00:27:56,091 --> 00:27:58,217
Carnell didn't have any time
to hang out with anybody.

602
00:27:58,344 --> 00:27:59,552
It's not fungus.

603
00:27:59,678 --> 00:28:00,970
I already told you that.

604
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:03,681
There's no pustules,
it's not staph.

605
00:28:06,435 --> 00:28:07,393
His dad's what?

606
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:09,937
His dad owns a scrap metal
salvage yard.

607
00:28:10,064 --> 00:28:12,106
Carnell worked there
during breaks.

608
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:19,655
You lied.

609
00:28:19,782 --> 00:28:20,990
What are you talking about?

610
00:28:21,116 --> 00:28:23,242
Oh, yeah, of course,
in this family,

611
00:28:23,369 --> 00:28:25,453
you probably
need more specifics.

612
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:28,748
You told us you owned a construction
company, not a salvage yard.

613
00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:30,166
I know the way things work.

614
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:32,794
The better my job, the
better my son gets treated.

615
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,462
Right, that's why I'm mad,

616
00:28:34,588 --> 00:28:36,964
we wasted all that
filet mignon on you.

617
00:28:37,091 --> 00:28:39,801
Did your kid find anything unusual
the last time he worked for you?

618
00:28:39,927 --> 00:28:40,927
No.

619
00:28:41,053 --> 00:28:41,969
Braided wire?

620
00:28:42,096 --> 00:28:44,555
Metal weights on each end, a
lead canister, maybe just a lid.

621
00:28:44,681 --> 00:28:46,641
Probably used it as a doorstop
or a paperweight.

622
00:28:46,767 --> 00:28:48,309
Why would he wanna...

623
00:28:50,104 --> 00:28:52,146
Okay, here it comes.

624
00:28:52,272 --> 00:28:53,981
I gave him
an early graduation gift,

625
00:28:54,108 --> 00:28:56,401
an old plumb I found,
looks like a fishing weight.

626
00:28:56,527 --> 00:28:59,987
Put it on a keychain, so he'd
always remember where he came from.

627
00:29:00,114 --> 00:29:01,989
So he could lie about it later?

628
00:29:02,116 --> 00:29:04,867
- Where's the keychain?
- I don't know, he never used it.

629
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:06,327
Just kept it
as a good luck charm.

630
00:29:06,453 --> 00:29:09,038
- Kept it where?
- I don't know.

631
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:11,999
Why? Why does it matter?

632
00:29:13,127 --> 00:29:14,248
Where are the kid's clothes?

633
00:29:14,336 --> 00:29:16,129
In the bureau
back in his regular room.

634
00:29:16,255 --> 00:29:18,714
- You two, get it to radiology.
- His clothes?

635
00:29:18,841 --> 00:29:20,800
The bureau. Don't open it.

636
00:29:20,926 --> 00:29:22,510
You, come with me.

637
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:29,892
Set it down there.

638
00:29:32,855 --> 00:29:35,565
Now get out of here,
this thing's radioactive.

639
00:29:35,691 --> 00:29:38,985
The chances of radiation
causing CNS symptoms?

640
00:29:43,157 --> 00:29:45,074
Whoa.

641
00:29:50,038 --> 00:29:52,582
Call the boys
in the lead pajamas.

642
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:07,638
The radiation measurements
weren't high enough

643
00:30:07,764 --> 00:30:10,057
to cause central
nervous system damage.

644
00:30:10,184 --> 00:30:11,624
It mightn't have caused
nerve damage,

645
00:30:11,685 --> 00:30:13,769
but it definitely destroyed
his immune system.

646
00:30:13,896 --> 00:30:15,229
And caused tumors.

647
00:30:15,355 --> 00:30:18,733
We don't know that. None of
the MRis showed anything.

648
00:30:20,194 --> 00:30:23,446
Do a PET scan.
Check his cervical spine.

649
00:30:24,948 --> 00:30:26,991
It's not gonna be good news.

650
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:32,747
Mr. Hall, it's not good news.

651
00:30:33,749 --> 00:30:35,708
The piece of metal
you gave Carnell

652
00:30:35,834 --> 00:30:38,920
was from an industrial device
used to test wells.

653
00:30:39,046 --> 00:30:41,631
People aren't supposed to just
dump radioactive material.

654
00:30:41,757 --> 00:30:43,007
But they do.

655
00:30:48,180 --> 00:30:50,640
So, what now?
I mean, what do you do?

656
00:30:50,766 --> 00:30:52,767
Anyone who's had
contact with the source

657
00:30:52,893 --> 00:30:56,062
will have to immediately get
treatment for radiation sickness.

658
00:30:56,188 --> 00:30:58,105
Taddy carried it
on his lap on the flight.

659
00:30:58,232 --> 00:30:59,982
So there is a treatment?

660
00:31:00,651 --> 00:31:02,318
Transfusions.

661
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:05,446
And we try to get the fluids
and electrolytes balanced.

662
00:31:05,572 --> 00:31:06,739
Carnell,

663
00:31:08,325 --> 00:31:10,243
he's had much more exposure.

664
00:31:10,369 --> 00:31:13,496
The equivalent of about
70,000 chest X rays.

665
00:31:14,206 --> 00:31:17,917
His ability to create white blood
cells has been completely destroyed.

666
00:31:18,835 --> 00:31:21,587
And that's why he can't
fight off this infection?

667
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:24,674
Yeah. He's gonna need
a bone marrow transplant.

668
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:29,720
And we did another PET scan.

669
00:31:29,846 --> 00:31:33,975
There's a cavernous angioma within
his spinal cord, it's a tumor.

670
00:31:34,101 --> 00:31:38,020
That's what's been causing
the shocks and CNS symptoms.

671
00:31:38,146 --> 00:31:41,607
He has a tumor
inside of his spinal cord?

672
00:31:42,734 --> 00:31:46,487
The cord is made of strands

673
00:31:46,613 --> 00:31:49,365
put together,
sort of like a kite string.

674
00:31:49,491 --> 00:31:54,036
The surgeon should be able to pull the
strands apart and excise the tumor.

675
00:31:54,162 --> 00:31:58,749
But surgery on someone who's as
hemopoetically compromised as your son

676
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:01,669
is extremely risky.

677
00:32:11,638 --> 00:32:12,763
And,

678
00:32:14,975 --> 00:32:17,643
if you don't do the surgery?
I mean...

679
00:32:17,769 --> 00:32:20,771
The tumor could cause
his breathing to stop.

680
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:23,232
Possibly his heart as well.

681
00:32:27,112 --> 00:32:29,739
There's no way
you could have known.

682
00:32:41,752 --> 00:32:43,502
Now, you're gonna
have to come with us.

683
00:32:43,629 --> 00:32:44,712
You need to start
treatment yourself.

684
00:32:44,838 --> 00:32:46,505
No. No, no.

685
00:32:47,758 --> 00:32:49,634
I can start my treatment later.

686
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,052
But he can't.

687
00:32:51,762 --> 00:32:55,848
He needs to be in a sterile isolation
room to prevent further infections.

688
00:33:03,023 --> 00:33:04,774
- Mom.
- We're early.

689
00:33:05,442 --> 00:33:08,402
- It's great to see you.
- Oh, Greg, don't lie.

690
00:33:11,573 --> 00:33:13,366
We came at a bad time,
didn't we?

691
00:33:13,492 --> 00:33:17,370
Actually, yeah, I think
I have to take a rain check.

692
00:33:17,496 --> 00:33:20,373
Oh, plans have been made.
Wilson made them.

693
00:33:21,083 --> 00:33:22,458
I asked him to cancel.

694
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:24,752
I'm dealing with a kind of a
complicated case right now so...

695
00:33:24,878 --> 00:33:26,587
Well, we'll just come back

696
00:33:26,713 --> 00:33:28,756
when things aren't
so out of control.

697
00:33:29,758 --> 00:33:31,175
My team is busy.

698
00:33:31,301 --> 00:33:32,468
You don't wanna see us.

699
00:33:32,594 --> 00:33:34,053
Mom, don't make me feel guilty.

700
00:33:34,179 --> 00:33:36,055
No, no, of course not. Sorry.

701
00:33:36,181 --> 00:33:39,266
I've got a patient who's probably
gonna die of radiation poisoning.

702
00:33:39,393 --> 00:33:41,560
So that means you can't eat?

703
00:33:43,063 --> 00:33:45,690
Come on, let's grab a
bite in the cafeteria.

704
00:33:45,816 --> 00:33:47,566
I'll buy you a Reuben.

705
00:33:51,279 --> 00:33:52,655
Well, I guess
I got time for a sandwich.

706
00:33:52,781 --> 00:33:53,781
Good.

707
00:33:57,786 --> 00:33:58,661
Yeah?

708
00:33:58,787 --> 00:34:00,121
I just wanted to let you know

709
00:34:00,247 --> 00:34:01,622
that Carnell's prepped
for surgery.

710
00:34:01,748 --> 00:34:03,124
Thank you.

711
00:34:04,751 --> 00:34:09,171
Hi, I'm Allison Cameron.
I work with your son.

712
00:34:09,297 --> 00:34:10,840
Greg's told us all about you.

713
00:34:10,966 --> 00:34:11,966
Really?

714
00:34:13,677 --> 00:34:14,635
New, huh?

715
00:34:14,761 --> 00:34:16,220
Nope, just gullible.

716
00:34:16,346 --> 00:34:19,056
I'm sorry, I was just
making fun of my son,

717
00:34:19,182 --> 00:34:20,641
not of you.

718
00:34:20,767 --> 00:34:22,852
We were just about to go
to get something to eat,

719
00:34:22,978 --> 00:34:24,645
would you care to join us?

720
00:34:28,316 --> 00:34:30,651
You don't have
a lot of time with your son.

721
00:34:30,777 --> 00:34:32,778
Maybe another time.

722
00:34:41,997 --> 00:34:45,040
- Do you like the Beatles?
- They're all right.

723
00:34:46,334 --> 00:34:49,295
My 12-year-old just turned
me back on to them.

724
00:34:51,757 --> 00:34:54,717
McCartney's gotta have
more money than God.

725
00:34:56,303 --> 00:34:58,929
I think that's all of it.
Reverse him.

726
00:35:00,056 --> 00:35:01,724
How's he doing?

727
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:06,353
- Looks pretty good down here.
- Do I rock, or what?

728
00:35:07,314 --> 00:35:08,939
His pressure's dropping!

729
00:35:09,065 --> 00:35:10,941
- Give him another two units.
- I did already!

730
00:35:11,067 --> 00:35:12,818
His heart rate's falling.

731
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:14,779
He's hemorrhaging.

732
00:35:22,871 --> 00:35:25,831
They're talking about Mom's
last trip to the dentist.

733
00:35:26,792 --> 00:35:28,667
Grown children
talking to their parents,

734
00:35:28,794 --> 00:35:30,377
nothing gets talked about.

735
00:35:30,504 --> 00:35:32,797
Trust me,
you're not missing anything.

736
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:36,884
So, besides work,
what you been up to?

737
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:38,052
Not much.

738
00:35:38,178 --> 00:35:40,679
You always say that,
"Not much".

739
00:35:41,306 --> 00:35:42,681
It's always the answer.

740
00:35:42,808 --> 00:35:45,309
Any new babes
you might wanna tell me about?

741
00:35:45,435 --> 00:35:47,311
Leave him alone, John.

742
00:35:48,188 --> 00:35:49,772
Got a new motorcycle.

