744
00:35:53,527 --> 00:35:55,694
it's orange
with a gigantic scrape.

745
00:35:55,821 --> 00:35:58,030
Is it the one
in the handicapped parking?

746
00:35:58,156 --> 00:35:59,240
Yeah.

747
00:35:59,991 --> 00:36:01,700
Looks like crap,
but it drives great.

748
00:36:01,827 --> 00:36:04,036
Well, you'll be careful, right?

749
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:06,664
Last I checked,
you still have two legs.

750
00:36:06,790 --> 00:36:08,040
Actually, three.

751
00:36:09,292 --> 00:36:10,960
You know what
your problem is, Greg?

752
00:36:11,086 --> 00:36:12,461
Shifting gears?

753
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:15,130
You just don't know
how lucky you are.

754
00:36:18,885 --> 00:36:20,678
Where's the head?

755
00:36:27,769 --> 00:36:29,770
Well, good thing
we got that cleared up.

756
00:36:29,896 --> 00:36:31,897
Oh, he was just trying to help.

757
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:33,566
I don't need help.

758
00:36:33,692 --> 00:36:34,942
I know.

759
00:36:35,068 --> 00:36:38,153
You're absolutely perfect
just the way you are.

760
00:36:55,672 --> 00:36:56,755
Thank you.

761
00:37:02,804 --> 00:37:05,806
So, how much longer do you
think he'll be in surgery?

762
00:37:05,932 --> 00:37:07,641
It's hard to say.

763
00:37:18,653 --> 00:37:21,655
You know, he just
started school when Ann died.

764
00:37:22,324 --> 00:37:23,699
I was a mess.

765
00:37:27,162 --> 00:37:30,623
Still adjusting to being a parent,
much less a single parent.

766
00:37:32,208 --> 00:37:36,378
You know, I used to put cold
pancakes in his lunch box.

767
00:37:37,881 --> 00:37:39,632
I mean, that was the only thing

768
00:37:39,758 --> 00:37:41,592
I could make that he would eat.

769
00:37:42,677 --> 00:37:45,429
- You did okay, he's a good kid.
- Yeah.

770
00:37:50,185 --> 00:37:53,312
Hey. So, how is he?

771
00:37:54,648 --> 00:37:57,316
Well, the surgeon
has removed the tumor

772
00:37:57,442 --> 00:37:59,485
without damaging
the spinal cord.

773
00:37:59,611 --> 00:38:02,154
But, the infection has caused

774
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:04,490
another intestinal perforation.

775
00:38:05,659 --> 00:38:06,619
We stopped the bleeding,

776
00:38:06,743 --> 00:38:08,744
but his white count
keeps falling.

777
00:38:08,870 --> 00:38:10,037
Okay.

778
00:38:13,208 --> 00:38:16,502
So what now? Another drug,
antibiotics, what?

779
00:38:19,214 --> 00:38:20,631
I'm sorry.

780
00:38:21,758 --> 00:38:23,968
The reality is,
no matter what we give him,

781
00:38:24,094 --> 00:38:27,888
it's unlikely he's gonna be able
to fight off the infections.

782
00:38:52,956 --> 00:38:54,415
Okay, okay.

783
00:39:01,381 --> 00:39:04,091
The father and the friend are
responding well to treatment.

784
00:39:04,217 --> 00:39:07,011
Things aren't looking
so good for Carnell.

785
00:39:08,388 --> 00:39:09,680
Thank you,

786
00:39:10,515 --> 00:39:11,974
for not eating.

787
00:39:14,853 --> 00:39:16,687
It was none of my business.

788
00:39:18,732 --> 00:39:20,983
They seem perfectly pleasant,
don't they?

789
00:39:21,693 --> 00:39:22,693
They are.

790
00:39:23,695 --> 00:39:26,780
He was a marine pilot.
She was a housewife.

791
00:39:27,782 --> 00:39:31,201
Married 47 years,
they had one child.

792
00:39:32,954 --> 00:39:34,663
Mom is just like everyone else,

793
00:39:35,707 --> 00:39:37,249
she's nice enough,

794
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:40,335
no great sense of humor,
hates confrontation.

795
00:39:41,713 --> 00:39:43,672
My dad's just like you.

796
00:39:44,424 --> 00:39:47,342
Not the caring till
your eyes pop out part,

797
00:39:48,261 --> 00:39:50,054
just the insane moral compass

798
00:39:50,180 --> 00:39:52,556
that won't let you lie
to anybody about anything.

799
00:39:52,682 --> 00:39:54,558
It's a great quality
for Boy Scouts

800
00:39:54,684 --> 00:39:56,143
and police witnesses.

801
00:39:58,104 --> 00:40:00,147
Crappy quality for a dad.

802
00:40:15,288 --> 00:40:16,413
Hey.

803
00:40:17,499 --> 00:40:18,665
How you doing?

804
00:40:19,292 --> 00:40:20,709
I'm hanging in there.

805
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:28,675
I'm sorry
I lied to you about Mom.

806
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:32,805
I'm sorry I lied to you, too.

807
00:40:35,558 --> 00:40:38,560
There was nothing good
that came out of her dying.

808
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:40,020
I'm not mad.

809
00:40:41,689 --> 00:40:43,649
I know why you did it.

810
00:40:45,693 --> 00:40:46,902
It worked.

811
00:40:48,738 --> 00:40:50,697
I never drink and drive.

812
00:40:57,205 --> 00:40:58,705
I'm scared, Dad.

813
00:41:03,336 --> 00:41:04,670
Come on.

814
00:41:06,339 --> 00:41:08,674
There's nothing
to be scared of.

815
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:11,176
You're gonna be just fine.

816
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:12,469
Don't play me.

817
00:41:14,264 --> 00:41:16,140
I wanna know the truth.

818
00:41:17,517 --> 00:41:19,560
I'm telling you the truth.

819
00:41:21,062 --> 00:41:23,689
You're gonna be fine, I swear.

820
00:41:30,697 --> 00:41:32,322
I love you, Dad.

821
00:41:34,701 --> 00:41:36,410
I love you, too.

822
00:41:51,801 --> 00:41:54,928
Why does he hate
seeing his parents?

823
00:41:55,054 --> 00:41:58,724
So his dad tells the truth,
he can't handle that?

824
00:41:58,850 --> 00:42:01,351
He hates
being a disappointment.

825
00:42:01,477 --> 00:42:03,854
He's a doctor, world famous.

826
00:42:04,981 --> 00:42:07,274
How disappointed can they be?

827
00:42:08,693 --> 00:42:10,068
You know what I figure is worse

828
00:42:10,195 --> 00:42:12,446
than watching your son
become crippled?

829
00:42:13,448 --> 00:42:15,532
Watching him be miserable.

